explanation: UT_COMPARE_TYPE (macro) — The switch dispatch is based on this macro; its definition must be inspected to ensure it does not expand to or call any function (e.g. memcmp) that would violate the MISRA rule. UtAssert_Compare_t (enum) and the individual compare constants (UtAssert_Compare_EQ, _NEQ, _LT, _GT, _LTEQ, _GTEQ, _BITMASK_SET, _BITMASK_UNSET) — The meanings/values of these constants determine which case labels are generated by UT_COMPARE_TYPE; confirm none map to an operation that uses memcmp or other string comparisons. UtAssert_IntBuf_t — Definition of this union/struct (and the types of its members .u and .s) is required to verify that comparisons in the function are integer comparisons (not pointer/char * comparisons or string buffers), so the code does not perform a string comparison via ==, <, etc., or indirectly via memcmp. UT_IntCheck_t — The typedef of ReferenceValueIn must be checked to ensure it is an integer type (not a pointer to char or string type) so that the comparisons here are numeric and not string comparisons. These symbols are sufficient to determine whether any of the switch/case expansions or the operand types could cause or hide use of memcmp (or any null-terminated string comparison) inside UtAssert_DoCompare.
